world <- map_data("world")

Data Analysis

View(founder_crops)
founder_crops_mutated <- founder_crops %>%
  mutate(age_start_num = as.numeric(age_start)) %>%
  mutate(age_end_num = as.numeric(age_end)) %>%
  mutate(longitude_num = as.numeric(longitude)) %>%
  mutate(latitude_num = as.numeric(latitude))

View(founder_crops_mutated)
map_coor <- data.frame(lon = 40, lat = 35)

base_map <- get_map(map_coor, zoom = 5, maptype = "watercolor")
## ! `maptype = "watercolor"` is only available with `source = "stamen"`; resetting source.
## ℹ <]8;;https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/staticmap?center=35,40&zoom=5&size=640x640&scale=2&maptype=terrain&key=xxxhttps://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/staticmap?center=35,40&zoom=5&size=640x640&scale=2&maptype=terrain&key=xxx]8;;>
## ℹ Map tiles by Stamen Design, under CC BY 3.0. Data by OpenStreetMap, under CC BY SA.
founder_crops_filtered <- filter(founder_crops_mutated, phase == "Abu Hureyra 1 (epipalaeolithic) phase 1")

base_map <- ggmap(base_map) +
  geom_point(data = founder_crops_filtered,
             aes(x = longitude, y = latitude, color = "red"),
             alpha = 0.25,
             size = 1,
             stroke = 1)
